The paper deals with secure positioning in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to both computer security (cs.CR) and networking (cs.NI). The use of distance evaluation techniques and protocols also suggests a focus on distributed systems (cs.DS) and systems engineering (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of information theory (cs.IT) in the discussion of the trusted sensor model.
